This file should have been included in the distribution but wasn&#39;t.  If  
you make a call to GRI30(), it should automatically create gri30.xml in  
the local directory. Alternatively, you can get it from the user&#39;s  
group site under &#39;Files&#39;.

Some of the examples require gri30.xml to already exist, but will not  
create it from gri30.cti if it is not found (this will be fixed). If  
you create gri30.xml, then simply move it to the data folder in order  
to run these examples from any directory.


